Our Products

Click Here for FAQs for Newcomers to SDR Receivers and SDRplay

WARNING: Beware FAKE and SDRplay “compatible” SDR products. Click on the warning triangle above for more information
The nRSP-ST is a truly “plug and play” integrated, networked general coverage receiver which combines a receiver, a host computer and a whole lot more all in one box. The receiver comprises a full-featured 14-bit software defined radio. It offers up to 10MHz of spectrum visibility anywhere between 1kHz and 2GHz.
The RSPdx-R2 is an enhanced version of the RSPdx. In addition to the functionality of the RSP1B, the RSPdx-R2 provides three software selectable antenna inputs and an optimised “HDR mode” below 2MHz. Click on the image above for more details
The RSP1B is an enhanced version of the popular RSP1A. The entry-level SDRplay RSP1B is a powerful wideband full-featured 14-bit SDR which covers the RF spectrum from 1kHz to 2GHz. Click on the image above for details
The RSPduo is a complete dual-tuner SDR receiver. In addition to 10MHz spectrum visibility it allows simultaneous monitoring of two completely seperate 2MHz bands of spectrum plus diversity tuning. Click on the image above for more details
When you buy an SDRplay product, you get free access to one-to-one help from our technical support staff in the UK and the USA. For non-English speaking customers there are many authorised resellers located around the world who can provide technical assistance.
Click here to try out an nRSP-ST networked receiver!
